V: \mathbb{R}^n \rightarrow \mathbb{R}
u: [0, + \infty) \rightarrow \mathbb{R}
u_0
\dot u(t) = - \nabla V(u(t)) 
u
v
w = u - v
w(0) = 0
w
 w' = u' - v' = -\nabla V u + \nabla V v. 
f(t) =  \left<w(t),w(t)\right>
f(0) = 0
f'
 f'(t) = 2\left<w'(t),w(t)\right> = -2\left<\nabla V u - \nabla V v,u - v\right> \leq - 2 C \left<u-v,u-v\right> = -2C f(t) 
